<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Warpgate 0.4 can now securely expose MySQL / RDS servers to remote users with 2FA and RBAC - and with no need for extra client-side software! And you can use it to connect app instances to their databases too.</p> <h2>About the project</h2> <p><a href="https://github.com/warp-tech/warpgate">https://github.com/warp-tech/warpgate</a></p> <p>Warpgate is a smart SSH, HTTPS and MySQL bastion host for Linux (and macOS!) that doesn&#39;t need special client apps.</p> <ul> <li>Set it up in your DMZ, add user accounts and easily assign them to specific hosts and URLs within the network.</li> <li>Warpgate will record every session for you to view (live) and replay later through a built-in admin web UI.</li> <li>Not a jump host - forwards your connections straight to the target instead.</li> <li>2FA support</li> <li>Single binary with no dependencies.</li> <li>Written in 100% safe Rust.</li> </ul> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/kebaabe"> /u/kebaabe </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/w9fb3p/warpgate_04_an_sshhttp_bastion_now_can_securely/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/w9fb3p/warpgate_04_an_sshhttp_bastion_now_can_securely/">[comments]</a></span>